{"key":"processedPost-8546633","value":{"id":8546633,"first":8545035,"last":8554353,"when":1214052930,"utime":"06/21/08 03:55 PM","cleanedPost":"The 'old' method was to apply the casing layer at the time the substrate was prepared, therefore you can case at 0% colonization if you want to.<br />However, since on the scale of time, mushroom growing remains in its infancy, we're still learning as we go along.&nbsp; We've found that if you colonize your substrate first, and then case it at full colonization, you'll be a bit more likely to get an even pinset.&nbsp; Don't stress it though, it's not about contamination.&nbsp; You can case the day your mix your spawn into the substrate if you wish.&nbsp; The casing layer will colonize as the substrate does, if you use that method.<br />RR"}}